UMCS.util
Interface TrieEnumerator

All Known Implementing Classes:
TrieEnum
public interface TrieEnumerator

Interface for representing enumerations of positions in a Trie. A Trie Enumerator can only be created by a Trie. For example: 

   Trie t = new CompressedTrie();
   ...
   TrieEnumerator enum = t.findPrefix("co");
   TriePos p = enum.getFirst();
   while (p!=null) {
      System.out.println(t.getString(p)+": "+t.getContent(p).toString());
      p=enum.getNext();
   }

Author:
Jeroen Donkers
See Also:
Trie, TriePos
